  "title": "refactor(helper): update listeners [PART-4]",
  "body": "This PR updates how we subscribe/use the listeners on the Helper. We moved away from [a list of arguments to an object](https://github.com/algolia/algoliasearch-helper-js/pull/700). The PR address those changes on the listeners. It also updates how the `error` event is emitted at the InstantSearch level. It now to match the shape of the Helper.\r\n\r\n```js\r\n// With list of arguments\r\nsearch.on('error', error => {\r\n  console.log(error);\r\n});\r\n\r\n// With an object\r\nsearch.on('error', event => {\r\n  console.log(event.error);\r\n});\r\n```\r\n\r\n> The CI does not pass, it's expected. It won't pass until the last PR of the stack.",
